Curtiss Aeroplane and Motor Company Logo Curtiss Aeroplane and Motor Company was an American aircraft manufacturer formed in 1916 by Glenn Hammond Curtiss. After significant commercial success in the ‘teens and 20s, it merged with the Wright Aeronautical in 1929 to form Curtiss-Wright Corporation. Source
